<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>NVRS Project - Development Journey</title>
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link href="/css/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <header class="blog-header py-3">
        <div class="row flex-nowrap justify-content-between align-items-center">
          <div class="col-4 pt-1">
            <a class="link-secondary" href="/">Back to Home</a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-4 text-center">
            <a class="blog-header-logo text-dark" href="/">NVRS Project</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>
    </div>

    <main class="container">
      <article class="blog-post">
        <h1 class="blog-post-title">NVRS: Evolution of a Full-Stack Project</h1>
        <p class="blog-post-meta">
          Project Overview by
          <a href="https://github.com/AlexanderTheNotSoBad-git">Alex</a>
        </p>

        <div class="row mb-4">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <h2>Project Background</h2>
            <p>
              The NVRS (Node.js Virtual Restaurant System) project represents my
              journey through modern web development technologies. Starting with
              vanilla JavaScript and evolving toward serverless architecture,
              this project demonstrates the natural progression of web
              application development in today's cloud-first world.
            </p>
            <div class="card text-center mb-4 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body bg-light">
                    <h4 class="card-title">Visit the Live Project</h4>
                    <p class="card-text">Experience the NVRS application in action</p>
                    <a href="https://vrsprototype.com" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Launch NVRS Demo</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <h2>Technical Evolution</h2>
            <div class="tech-reference">
              <h3>Phase 1: Foundation (Vanilla JS)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Express.js server handling route logic</li>
                <li>MySQL database for data persistence</li>
                <li>Basic client-side JavaScript for interactivity</li>
                <li>Bootstrap for responsive design</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-reference">
              <h3>Phase 2: Modern Framework (Next.js)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Server-side rendering with Next.js</li>
                <li>Enhanced routing capabilities</li>
                <li>Improved state management</li>
                <li>Better code organization and maintainability</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-reference">
              <h3>Phase 3: Future Direction (AWS Lambda)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Transitioning to serverless architecture</li>
                <li>Implementing C# Lambda functions</li>
                <li>API Gateway integration</li>
                <li>Cloud-native scaling capabilities</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>Key Features</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Secure user authentication system</li>
              <li>RESTful API design principles</li>
              <li>Responsive UI across devices</li>
              <li>Scalable database architecture</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Development Insights</h3>
            <p>
              The transition from vanilla JavaScript to Next.js revealed the
              advantages of modern frameworks in managing complex applications.
              The upcoming move to AWS Lambda represents our commitment to
              scalable, maintainable architecture.
            </p>

            <h3>Future Enhancements</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Serverless function implementation</li>
              <li>Enhanced API documentation</li>
              <li>Advanced caching mechanisms</li>
              <li>Performance monitoring integration</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="position-sticky" style="top: 2rem">
              <div class="p-4 mb-3 bg-light rounded">
                <h4>Project Links</h4>
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/AlexanderTheNotSoBad-git>GitHub Repository</a>
                  </li>
                  <li><a href="https://vrsprototype.com">Live Demo</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="p-4">
                <h4>Tech Stack</h4>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0">
                  <li>Node.js</li>
                  <li>Express</li>
                  <li>MySQL</li>
                  <li>Next.js</li>
                  <li>AWS Lambda (Coming Soon)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>

    <footer class="blog-footer">
      <p><a href="#">Back to top</a></p>
    </footer>

